I'm also graduated as a Nutritionist, so my passions really are Fashion, Beauty and Health. I'm now back in the Netherlands, and I'm pregnant with our first child!

bio:
My name is Sunny Gu, a Los Angeles-based fashion & beauty illustrator. 

I have been commissioned by the likes of Condé Nast, Vogue Magazine, Teen Vogue, ELLE Magazine , InStyle, Bloomingdales, Macy's, Nordstrom, Versace, Dolce & Gabbana's Swide Magazine, Carolina Herrera, Brian Atwood, Express, South Coast Plaza, Beverly Center,The Grove, La Prairie, Shiseido, FANCL , Neutrogena and HBO among others. 

I was born and raised in China, I moved to the United States when I was 13. After encountering people from different backgrounds, I became very curious about other cultures. I learned to observe and discover beauties in everything around me. 

I wish to find a way to capture and preserve the beauties that I see, the kindness that I feel, and recreate them in someway. I decided to become an illustrator and artist. 

For most of my illustrations, I paint them in watercolor. I love the vibrancy and unpredictable nature of watercolor. Occasionally I use graphite or acrylic paint to render some special textures. I also create digital art for surface design and textiles. 

My illustrations are always full of vibrant colors, rich details and delightful feelings. My work, on the other hand, is an endless journey searching for beauty, value, truth and self. When I paint, I am bathed in happiness, I hope my colorful illustrations can bring you some joy too! 

Wish you a wonderful day! 

Sunny

bio:

The store heavily relies on trend forecasts where the seasonal vintage buys reflect up to date fashion movements whilst remaining unique and one of a kind. 
Rachel’s coordination with designers, labels, style icons, photographers, bloggers and PR companies across the globe ensures that the shop will forever offer eccentric pieces like no other and the Tuesday Vintage platform will constantly be showcasing the best of the best. 

Much like most age old tales - there is a beginning, a middle and an end. 
For Tuesday Vintage, this is only the beginning. 

Thankful to everyone who has joined this wild adventure, Rachel truly believes it's all of the people she has met along the way that keeps this inspiration and magic growing.. ♡

name: Lindsi Lane•So|Lindsi
bio:
Lindsi Lane is on a mission to prove that with the right outfit, a good attitude and a sense of humor, anything is possible. The New York City-based writer is the founder of lifestyle website, SoLindsi.com, a carefully curated edit of personal stories, satirical commentary, and outfit inspiration. Lindsi draws upon her fashion background and straight-shooting persona to create Humor with a Sense of Style. 

The Indiana University-grad began her fashion career working for Gucci, Michael Kors, and Elle magazine, before becoming the youngest personal shopper in Barney’s New York history at age 23. She went on to form styling company, Lindsi Michelle Lane LLC, and was signed as the first ‘By Appointment’ stylist for Ford Artists NYC. Despite her successful styling career, Lindsi was eager to show others that personal style extends far beyond the clothing on your back. 

In 2015, she launched SoLindsi.com to connect with readers as a digital hybrid of their best friend and stylist. “Style is how you paint your blank canvas, but your voice is the essence of your personal style,” says Lindsi, who empowers readers with her quick-witted charm and honest content – think Sex and the City meets Amy Schumer. “My mission is to inspire people to be comfortable in their own skin, embrace who they are beyond the surface, and laugh along the way.” 

SoLindsi.com is a lifestyle website best known for its Humor with a Sense of Style. Creator, Lindsi Lane shares personal narratives, candid advice with her Ask Lindsi column, fashion finds, and relationship advice to help readers develop a bold, eccentric style that celebrates originality and cultivates confidence. Her witty perspective and relatable point of view sets the site apart from others in the digital space. name: Berlin based fashion hunter
bio:
Hello everyone, I’m Amelie, 24 years old, transylvanian girl raised in Italy and now living in Berlin. I just graduated in business administration but fashion has always been one of my biggest passions. 
Fashion industry intrigues me as well, in particular marketing, branding and sales strategies. This is one of the reasons that I started my influencer career. 
Influencer market it’s interesting to me because it’s a new way to connect with the customer. It opens a brand new space for the brands where they can create an authentic interaction with their customers. 
What also interests me a lot, as a woman, it’s the female model that a brand represents. I’m focused on female rights and how our figure is showed into an advertisement. 
My project started officially 6 months ago through Instagram, which offers the perfect platform where the relationship between brands and influencer can raise. I’m working now on a new website that would be a portfolio of my partnerships with a description of the brand (a paragraph where I write about its history, its goals and its ideals - for ex. which kind of woman could fit in my opinion with that specific kind of brand: comfy girl, chic business woman, sporty fitness etc etc). 
I’m looking for a brand interested in investing in influencing marketing and I’d love creating a long term collaboration, so the people who follow me on social channels can identify my style into the brand’s style, and they know that if they’re interested in having news about the brand they can find them also from me. My focus is building a real and interactive relationship with my followers, so what I can offer in a collaboration is an authentic audience.

name: Nico Sesé, SFNYC
bio:
Nico Sese is a fashion professional with experience in fashion styling and consulting, model development, casting, and marketing. 

He began his fashion career in 2004 going to local talent schools around the San Francisco Bay Area for modeling and acting, in which he later found himself represented by a local agency. Sese began styling with his own projects for his modeling portfolio, then evolving to styling shoots for agencies' new faces. Since then, he has collaborated with many talented artists and has styled for photoshoots, fashion shows, and personal clients for events throughout San Francisco, developing a passion and meticulous eye for Fashion. 

Sese attended the Fashion Institute of Design and Merchandising in San Francisco the summer of 2010 and graduated in 2012 with an Associate of Arts Degree in Merchandise Marketing. While attending the Institute, he interned as a Merchandise Visual Associate at the corporate offices of Gap Inc. assisting in developing visual directives for North America and Canada. Shortly after the internship was completed, he went to extend his expertise to brands like Diesel, All Saints, Bloomingdales, and Sak’s Inc. 

In January of 2016, he set off to New York to further pursue his career in fashion where he’s worked with international casting directors, designers, photographers, stylists, makeup artists, hair-stylists, and other amazing talents. 

Now based in New York, Sese is a part-time Vintage Specialist at What Goes Around Comes Around and continues to work with industry professionals to develop his creativity, versatility, and knowledge.

We are a photography couple/duo from a little suburban area outside of Houston, Texas. We started making photography into a small business after we started dating and realized we both had a passion for it. Our different creative ideas come together to balance each other and we see small details that the other may not have noticed. Our couple dynamic helps us to put our clients at ease when shooting and also to give us multiple perspectives and ideas when shooting. 

Outside of photography, we love cooking (we often post our daily recipes on our Instagram story), traveling (our ultimate goal this summer is to go to Iceland), fashion, and just adventuring in general. We shoot not only to make money, but to have fun and express ourselves creatively in one of our favorite ways. Our shoots give us ways to fill our days and weekends with work, fun, and creative creation. 

We’ve worked with several small brands in Austin, from salons, to personal trainers, and even massage therapists. We also make sure to form quality, personal relationships with our clients so everyone is transparent about how they feel and what they want. Our clients have turned into some of our closest friends from time to time, as our concerted effort to build relationships has revealed that our clients are very similar to us and love the same things we do. It’s also refreshing to know that you’re not only making a product for someone, but you’re also making a bond with them that will allow for the best outcome between the two of you.

bio:
Fernando Consagra es un reconocido actor y modelo argentino, egresado del Centro de Educación Artística de Televisa. 

Fernando Consagra inicio su carrera como modelo pasarela, campañas publicitarias, y desde entonces ha servido como imagen de diferentes marcas como Aldo Conti, Blue Shield Blue Cross, Lady Speed. 

Luego es elegido por la cantante Maite Perroni para ser su Galán en su videoClip “Vas a querer Volver” 

En el 2002 inicia su carrera como actor de Cine protagonizando la película La Prueba del director Lucas Giuggia, la cual fue ganadora del premio Martín Fierro como mejor película. 

Más adelante viaja a México para internacionalizar su carrera, y en el 2008 incursiona como actor de Hollywood en el film The Informers (Los Confidentes), del director Gregor Jordan. 

Luego de terminar sus estudios en el Centro de Educación Artística de Televisa (CEA), comienza su trabajo en diferentes Novelas,Series, Cine y Teatro.

bio: My style isn’t set, so I style how I feel or what the day looks like. Sometimes I dress classy other times I dress more street. name: ha.ppiness
bio:
Hello, my name is Lili, I'm nearly 18 and I as born and raised in Vienna, Austria where I still gratefully live to this day. Thanks for stepping by to get o know me a lil better! :) 

As you may be able to tell from my Instagram, I'm very into photography and that's why I invested in a Nikon d3300 camera in march which comes everywhere I go.I do not only take loads of photos with it, no, I also record videos and cut them together afterwrads, making little films to remember wonderful days etc. I guess it's the pre-step to starting youtube which I'm planning to do next summer after I gratuated. Although I adore my camera with all my heart, I wish I also had a polaroid camera to catch the most unique moments in life since it's a special capture you can only make once! 

Something that really defines me as a person is my love for animals which is also the reason I'm an ethical vegan. Through that lifestyle I discovered my love for sports, healthy, plant-based food and my passion for cooking. I try to spread the message of compassion towards vegansim through my social medias. 

In addition I have to mention that I love fashion a lot and I can't really put my style into a certain category since it changes every day but I definitely prefer vintage clothing over brand new clothes. I love defining myself new everyday through combining different pieces for example. 

Another hobby of mine is journaling and penpaling where I can express my creativity on paper with my beloved stationary of which I can never have enough. The best way to express my feelings on paper, on the other hand side, is writing. I have been inspired to create stories in my head and write them down since I was in primary school and haven't stopped being since. 

I'm looking forward to working with companies that match my interests and hobbies! :)
